        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2064762407" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6143197257759265273">As a NYC history and baseball fan, this book is made for me. I can see why this was made into a mini-series. There&apos;s so much to work with and it&apos;s all interesting. The book does a good job in getting the broad strokes for many stories and players involved and it reads like a magazine article. The key is that it rarely feels too simplified. It flows well and you get the point and it&apos;s all interesting. I&apos;m intrigued by the vastness of NYC and this book does a good job in getting that across while </span>
  <span id="freeText6143197257759265273" style="display:none">As a NYC history and baseball fan, this book is made for me. I can see why this was made into a mini-series. There's so much to work with and it's all interesting. The book does a good job in getting the broad strokes for many stories and players involved and it reads like a magazine article. The key is that it rarely feels too simplified. It flows well and you get the point and it's all interesting. I'm intrigued by the vastness of NYC and this book does a good job in getting that across while never losing focus on the main stories. There are a couple of tangets such as with gentrification but they make complete sense in regard to how the city was dealing with white flight. The ending chapters do feel a bit slim but the story lines were done so it was time to get out. I wish I could get the next book in this style for the 80's.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6143197257759265273" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


